# Clip Maker Export

## Scope

Browser-rendered Twick frame capture, media transfer, backend validation, and
ffmpeg MP4 finalization.

## Load when

Changing clip-maker export, Twick frame/audio capture, `/clip-maker/export/frames`,
ffmpeg rendering, or temporary export downloads.

## Owns

- Frontend protocol writer: `frontend/src/pages/clip-maker/utils/exportUpload.ts`
- Export orchestration: `frontend/src/pages/clip-maker/hooks/useClipExport.ts`
- Backend protocol reader: `backend/internal/clipmaker/handler.go`
- ffmpeg finalizer: `backend/internal/videorenderer/browser_recording.go`
- Route: `POST /clip-maker/export/frames`

## Contracts

- The request body is `application/octet-stream` with newline-delimited JSON
  headers followed by exact-length binary payloads and a newline delimiter.
- The first record is metadata with dimensions, FPS, duration, frame count, and
  audio-record count. Ordered PNG frame records follow, then ordered audio records.
- Audio records carry source bytes plus timeline start/end, source trim, playback
  rate, and volume. Both Twick audio and audible video elements may contribute.
- The browser fetches media bytes. The backend never resolves project-provided URLs.
- The backend validates record order, lengths, PNG data/dimensions, timing, rate,
  volume, track count, and total request size before invoking ffmpeg.
- ffmpeg builds H.264/yuv420p video, trims and offsets each audio input, mixes all
  active inputs, encodes AAC at 192 kbps, and limits output to the frame duration.
- A project with no active audio produces a valid video-only MP4.
- Streaming upload is attempted first. Browser/proxy transport failure retries the
  same protocol as a buffered Blob without building video in the frontend.

## Invariants

- Export requests require JWT authentication and remain capped at 512 MiB.
- At most 32 audio records are accepted; each is capped at 128 MiB.
- Export duration is positive and at most ten minutes.
- Authentication headers are never forwarded to cross-origin media hosts.
- Workspaces and temporary render outputs are removed after request completion.

